Support Dr Ken Harvey - 简介 | Facebook








Facebook邮箱或手机号密码忘记帐户？注册首页简介照片视频社群点评帖子创建主页简介编辑建议更多信息简介Ongoing insight into the work of Dr. Ken Harvey in challenging shonky therapeutic products and keeping the public informed.个人简介*This page is run only by supporters of Ken Harvey, and was set up without request. We also support the great work Ken does and the many contributions he has ma...de*  Whilst Ken's problems with the initial catalyst for this page genesis have passed as of February 10th 2012, his work and wonderfully educational commentary continues.   +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ What follows is the original biography for this page:  SensaSlim is an alternative weight loss product that has drawn much media attention in Australia, giving the public an impression of seemingly miraculous success. Apart from making claims that defied the accepted science of weight loss, the marketers of SensaSlim claimed via a slick advertising campaign, video and website to have evidence gained from a clinical trial involving 11,000 people that the product was perhaps "the greatest weight loss product in the world".   In a May 31st 2011 article The Australian Skeptics revealed that Dr. Ken Harvey - an adjunct senior lecturer in the School of Public Health, La Trobe University - had complained to The Therapeutic Goods Administration over promotion of the product. This resulted in a strategic lawsuit against public participation, known as a 'SLAPP' suit, being lodged against Ken Harvey which causes significant financial and personal pressure. In a statement to the TGA's Complaints Resolution Panel, Dr. Harvey substantially backed his position that, “in my opinion, the ‘sensational results’ claimed are most likely to have been fabricated. In addition, I do not believe that any of the other claims made for this product are capable of substantiation.”  Before the CRP could deliberate adequately, SensaSlim issued a "Statement of claim" in the NSW Supreme court. This alleged defamation against Dr. Harvey, seeking “general and punitive damages for libel in the sum of $800,000.00”, plus costs, as reported by The Australian Skeptics.  Due to a clause in the Therapeutic Goods Regulations 1990 42ZCAJ (2) this puts a temporary but potentially lengthy stop to complaints heard by the CRP. As complaints can take months to reach conclusion the product is continued to be marketed and sold with no regard to it's legitimacy or indeed any possible negative effects. The relevant regulation states:  “If, after a complaint has been made to the Panel, a proceeding begins in a court about the subject matter of the complaint, the Panel cannot deal with the complaint until the proceeding is finally disposed of”.   Crucially, SensaSlim until May 21st, 2011 had Dr Matthew Capehorn, clinical director of the National Obesity Forum (UK) and clinical manager of the Rotherham Institute for Obesity, as their own Research Director. As part of this role Dr. Capehorn wrote and published a white paper on the unseen clinical trial evidence "in good faith". Through his lawyers Capehorn has written to SensaSlim stating in part, "Despite requests, I have never seen evidence of the original clinical trial, and it has never been published in a peer reviewed medical journal. Therefore, the White Paper holds no scientific relevance, until that original trial is published.”   SensaSlim have made numerous breaches of contract with Dr. Capehorn and have not acquiesced to his demands to remove his image, name and white paper from their website. You can read more about this at The Australian Skeptics by following - http://www.skeptics.com.au/latest/announcements/featured-announcement/ken-harvey-taken-to-court/  Due to obvious financial demands The Australian Skeptics have instituted a program for individuals to make a pledge simply by emailing supportken@skeptics.com.au with name, pledge and address. 展开获奖Read a full run down at Australian Skeptics - "Ken Harvey taken to court": http://www.skeptics.com.au/latest/announcements/featured-announcement/ken-harvey-taken-to-court/个人信息Dr. Ken Harvey is an adjunct senior lecturer in the School of Public Health, La Trobe University. He campaigns regularly against the nonscientific products and ...services that have become so pervasive in Australia over recent years. Dr. Harvey devotes much of his free time to speak to local skeptic groups and explain to relevant media outlets about the shortfalls in current legislation that have allowed the seeming unchecked growth of arguably unacceptable and ineffective products and services. In fact on December 6th last year "Pharma in Focus" revealed that "up to 90% of complementary medicines reviewed by the TGA do not comply with regulatory requirements".   Dr. Harvey is a frequent figure on TV, radio and in print media discussing the health, legal, financial and regulatory dynamics peculiar to Australia's apparent obsession with unproven and often untested New Age "therapies". 展开categories非营利组织中文(简体)English (US)日本語한국어Français (France)Bahasa IndonesiaPolskiEspañolPortuguês (Brasil)DeutschItalianoMessengerFacebook Lite用户地点游戏位置名人二手市场小组食谱彩色气球Instagram公司简介创建广告创建主页开发者招聘信息隐私权政策Cookie广告选项条款设置活动日志 Facebook © 2017



